500 g Ground Beef
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
4 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Lemon
113 g Baby Tomatoes
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Baby Spinach
½ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1.5 tbsp Oil*

Add breadcrumbs, Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend, two-thirds of the Zesty Garlic Blend, half the feta and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt to a medium bowl. (TIP: If you prefer more tender patties, add an egg to mixture.) Reserve remaining feta to serve in step 6.
Crumble in beef, then combine.
Form mixture into four (eight) 4-inch-wide patties.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then patties. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, cook patties in 2 batches, using 1/2 tbsp oil per batch.)
Pan-fry until golden-brown, 2-3 min per side.
Meanwhile, core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Add peppers, remaining Zesty Garlic Blend and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to one side of a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with pepper, then toss to coat. Set aside.

Transfer seared patties to the other side of the baking sheet with peppers.
Roast in the middle of the oven until peppers are tender and patties are cooked through, 10-12 min.**

Meanwhile, zest, then juice half the lemon. Cut remaining lemon into wedges.
Halve tomatoes.
Add mayo, lemon zest and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) lemon juice to a small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lemon juice and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. (TIP: Add a pinch of sugar to dressing, if desired.)
Add tomatoes and spinach, then toss to combine.

Divide patties, peppers and salad between plates.
Sprinkle remaining feta over salad.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if desired.
Serve lemony mayo alongside for dipping.

If you've opted for double beef, add an extra 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt to the beef mixture. Form mixture into four (eight) 4-inch-wide patties.